Architecture plan for issues #69-#71

Project shape
- Vite + React + TypeScript single-page app.
- Habit domain types live in src/types/habit.ts.
- Persistent local-first state and sample data live in src/stores/habitStore.ts and src/stores/seed.ts.
- Heatmap UI lives in src/components/HeatmapCalendar.tsx, with component tests in src/components/HeatmapCalendar.test.tsx.
- Pure date/stat/streak helpers live under src/utils.

Issue dependencies and implementation order
1. #69 changes the heatmap display window by updating HEATMAP_TRAILING_DAYS in src/components/HeatmapCalendar.tsx from 365 to 133.
2. #70 expands seeded check-in history in src/stores/seed.ts so demo habits visibly fill the revised ~133-day window; target roughly 150 days of source history so the full window has meaningful data.
3. #71 updates HeatmapCalendar tests in the same merge window as #69 so hard-coded date/count assertions match the 133-day window. This must land with #69 to avoid CI failures.

Key design decisions
- Keep the heatmap implementation centralized around HEATMAP_TRAILING_DAYS; avoid adding responsive scrolling or cloneElement/useEffect/useRef behavior outside the requested scope.
- Preserve existing date-key semantics: local yyyy-MM-dd keys generated by src/utils/date.ts and date-fns helpers.
- Keep seed data deterministic in shape but relative to today, matching current seed.ts style.
- Update tests only where expectations derive directly from HEATMAP_TRAILING_DAYS; do not change aria labels, tooltips, toggle behavior, or stats/streak logic.
- No new runtime dependencies are needed for these issues.
